## PAINTBRAIN LESSON вҖ” DO NOT REPEAT

PaintBrain was built without user scoping from day one. When other users were added later, admin data (Alan's personal settings, receipts, API tokens) leaked across user boundaries. This created weeks of cleanup work.

**Scatterbrain avoids this entirely by design:**
- There is no user table. There are no user accounts.
- Each user's data lives in THEIR cloud storage, completely isolated.
- The server never sees, stores, or routes user data.
- If two people install the app and connect their own Google Drives, their data never touches the same system.

This is the cleanest possible architecture for data isolation. Don't add a user database. Don't add server-side receipt storage. If you feel the urge to store something on the server, stop and ask: can this live in IndexedDB + cloud instead? The answer is almost always yes.

The ONE exception is the OCR proxy route (`/api/ocr/receipt`), which forwards images to OpenAI. This is stateless вҖ” the image goes in, the parsed JSON comes out, nothing is stored. If API cost tracking becomes important later, add a lightweight counter, but don't build a user system around it.

